  "sections": [
    {
      "type": "grammarIntro",
      "title": "Expanding Your Sentences",
      "icon": "📌",
      "summary": "These six particles let you add items, list things, talk about time ranges, and pin actions to specific days.",
      "whyItMatters": "With も, と, and や you can connect ideas and list items. With から and まで you can describe time ranges. And with に you can say exactly which day or date something happens — essential for talking about weekly schedules and monthly routines.",
      "youWillLearn": [
        "も — adding 'also' or 'too' (replaces は/が/を)",
        "と — listing things completely, or doing something 'with' someone",
        "や — listing things as examples (an incomplete list)",
        "から — marking a starting point ('from')",
        "まで — marking an ending point ('until')",
        "に — marking a specific day or date ('on Monday', 'on the 1st')"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "grammarRule",
      "id": "rule_mo_also",
      "pattern": [
        {
          "label": "NOUN",
          "color": "topic",
          "text": "X"
        },
        {
          "label": "PARTICLE",
          "color": "connector",
          "text": "も"
        },
        {
          "label": "PREDICATE",
          "color": "verb",
          "text": "..."
        }
      ],
      "meaning": "'X also / X too / even X ...'",
      "explanation": "も replaces は, が, or を to add the meaning 'also' or 'too'. It cannot be stacked on top of those particles — it replaces them. When used with negatives, も means 'either' or 'not even'.",
      "notes": [
        "も REPLACES は/が/を — do not write わたしはも or わたしがも.",
        "Positive + も = 'also': わたしもがくせいです (I'm also a student).",
        "Negative + も = 'either/not even': 父もわかりません (My father doesn't understand either)."
      ],
      "examples": [
        {
          "parts": [
            {
              "text": "わたし",
              "role": "topic",
              "gloss": "I"
            },
            {
              "text": "も",
              "role": "particle"
            },
            {
              "text": "がくせい",
              "role": "predicate",
              "gloss": "student"
            },
            {
              "text": "です",
              "role": "verb"
            }
          ],
          "en": "I am also a student.",
          "breakdown": "も replaces は — 'I too, am a student'"
        },
        {
          "parts": [
            {
              "text": "友だち",
              "role": "topic",
              "gloss": "friend"
            },
            {
              "text": "も",
              "role": "particle"
            },
            {
              "text": "やさしい",
              "role": "predicate",
              "gloss": "kind"
            },
            {
              "text": "です",
              "role": "verb"
            }
          ],
          "en": "My friend is also kind."
        },
        {
          "parts": [
            {
              "text": "土よう日",
              "role": "topic",
              "gloss": "Saturday"
            },
            {
              "text": "も",
              "role": "particle"
            },
            {
              "text": "いい",
              "role": "predicate",
              "gloss": "good"
            },
            {
              "text": "です",
              "role": "verb"
            }
          ],
          "en": "Saturday is also fine.",
          "breakdown": "も replaces は — 'Saturday too, is fine'"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "grammarRule",
      "id": "rule_to_and_with",
      "pattern": [
        {
          "label": "NOUN A",
          "color": "topic",
          "text": "A"
        },
        {
          "label": "PARTICLE",
          "color": "connector",
          "text": "と"
        },
        {
          "label": "NOUN B",
          "color": "topic",
          "text": "B"
        }
      ],
      "meaning": "'A and B' (complete list) / 'together with'",
      "explanation": "と connects nouns to mean 'and'. Unlike English, と lists things completely — A と B means 'A and B, and nothing else.' と can also mean 'together with' a person.",
      "notes": [
        "Complete listing: 母と父 means 'mother AND father' — just those two, no one else.",
        "Together with: 友だちと いっしょに means 'together with a friend'.",
        "You can chain: A と B と C (A and B and C)."
      ],
      "examples": [
        {
          "parts": [
            {
              "text": "母",
              "role": "topic",
              "gloss": "mother"
            },
            {
              "text": "と",
              "role": "connector"
            },
            {
              "text": "父",
              "role": "topic",
              "gloss": "father"
            },
            {
              "text": "は",
              "role": "particle"
            },
            {
              "text": "先生",
              "role": "predicate",
              "gloss": "teacher"
            },
            {
              "text": "です",
              "role": "verb"
            }
          ],
          "en": "My mother and father are teachers.",
          "breakdown": "と links two nouns completely: mother and father (just them)"
        },
        {
          "parts": [
            {
              "text": "月よう日",
              "role": "topic",
              "gloss": "Monday"
            },
            {
              "text": "と",
              "role": "connector"
            },
            {
              "text": "水よう日",
              "role": "topic",
              "gloss": "Wednesday"
            },
            {
              "text": "と",
              "role": "connector"
            },
            {
              "text": "金よう日",
              "role": "topic",
              "gloss": "Friday"
            }
          ],
          "en": "Monday, Wednesday, and Friday.",
          "breakdown": "と chains nouns in a complete list"
        },
        {
          "parts": [
            {
              "text": "友だち",
              "role": "topic",
              "gloss": "friend"
            },
            {
              "text": "と",
              "role": "connector"
            },
            {
              "text": "いっしょに",
              "role": "modifier",
              "gloss": "together"
            }
          ],
          "en": "Together with a friend.",
          "breakdown": "と + いっしょに = 'together with'"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "grammarRule",
      "id": "rule_ya_and_examples",
      "pattern": [
        {
          "label": "NOUN A",
          "color": "topic",
          "text": "A"
        },
        {
          "label": "PARTICLE",
          "color": "connector",
          "text": "や"
        },
        {
          "label": "NOUN B",
          "color": "topic",
          "text": "B"
        }
      ],
      "meaning": "'A, B, etc.' (incomplete list — and others)",
      "explanation": "や connects nouns like と, but implies there are more items not mentioned. A や B means 'things like A and B (and others).' It gives examples from a larger set.",
      "notes": [
        "Incomplete list: 先生や友だち means 'people like my teacher, my friends, (and others)'.",
        "Often appears with など (etc.): Aや Bなど.",
        "Use や when you're giving a representative sample, not an exhaustive list."
      ],
      "examples": [
        {
          "parts": [
            {
              "text": "先生",
              "role": "topic",
              "gloss": "teacher"
            },
            {
              "text": "や",
              "role": "connector"
            },
            {
              "text": "友だち",
              "role": "topic",
              "gloss": "friend"
            }
          ],
          "en": "Teachers, friends, (and others).",
          "breakdown": "や implies more people exist beyond those named"
        },
        {
          "parts": [
            {
              "text": "月よう日",
              "role": "topic",
              "gloss": "Monday"
            },
            {
              "text": "や",
              "role": "connector"
            },
            {
              "text": "木よう日",
              "role": "topic",
              "gloss": "Thursday"
            }
          ],
          "en": "Days like Monday, Thursday, (and others).",
          "breakdown": "や gives examples — other days are implied"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "grammarComparison",
      "title": "と vs や — Complete List vs Examples",
      "items": [
        {
          "label": "と — Complete List",
          "color": "connector",
          "points": [
            "Lists ALL items — nothing else is implied",
            "A と B = exactly A and B",
            "Also means 'together with' a person"
          ],
          "example": {
            "parts": [
              {
                "text": "母",
                "role": "topic"
              },
              {
                "text": "と",
                "role": "connector"
              },
              {
                "text": "父",
                "role": "topic"
              }
            ],
            "en": "Mother and father. (just those two)"
          }
        },
        {
          "label": "や — Sample List",
          "color": "connector",
          "points": [
            "Lists EXAMPLES — implies other items exist",
            "A や B = things like A and B (and more)",
            "Cannot mean 'together with'"
          ],
          "example": {
            "parts": [
              {
                "text": "母",
                "role": "topic"
              },
              {
                "text": "や",
                "role": "connector"
              },
              {
                "text": "父",
                "role": "topic"
              }
            ],
            "en": "People like my mother, father, (and others)."
          }
        }
      ],
      "tip": "Naming everything? → と. Giving examples from a bigger group? → や."
    },
    {
      "type": "grammarRule",
      "id": "rule_kara_made",
      "pattern": [
        {
          "label": "START",
          "color": "modifier",
          "text": "A"
        },
        {
          "label": "PARTICLE",
          "color": "connector",
          "text": "から"
        },
        {
          "label": "END",
          "color": "modifier",
          "text": "B"
        },
        {
          "label": "PARTICLE",
          "color": "connector",
          "text": "まで"
        }
      ],
      "meaning": "'from A to/until B'",
      "explanation": "から marks a starting point ('from') and まで marks an ending point ('until' or 'as far as'). They are often used together to describe a range, especially for time. Each can also be used alone.",
      "notes": [
        "から alone: 月よう日から (from Monday).",
        "まで alone: 金よう日まで (until Friday).",
        "Together: 月よう日から金よう日まで (from Monday to Friday).",
        "までに means 'by' (a deadline): 金よう日までに = by Friday."
      ],
      "examples": [
        {
          "parts": [
            {
              "text": "月よう日",
              "role": "time",
              "gloss": "Monday"
            },
            {
              "text": "から",
              "role": "particle"
            },
            {
              "text": "金よう日",
              "role": "time",
              "gloss": "Friday"
            },
            {
              "text": "まで",
              "role": "particle"
            }
          ],
          "en": "From Monday to Friday.",
          "breakdown": "から = starting point, まで = ending point"
        },
        {
          "parts": [
            {
              "text": "今日",
              "role": "time",
              "gloss": "today"
            },
            {
              "text": "から",
              "role": "particle"
            },
            {
              "text": "毎日",
              "role": "time",
              "gloss": "every day"
            }
          ],
          "en": "From today, every day.",
          "breakdown": "から marks the starting point of a routine"
        },
        {
          "parts": [
            {
              "text": "今月",
              "role": "time",
              "gloss": "this month"
            },
            {
              "text": "まで",
              "role": "particle"
            }
          ],
          "en": "Until this month.",
          "breakdown": "まで alone marks the end point"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "grammarRule",
      "id": "rule_ni_time",
      "pattern": [
        {
          "label": "SPECIFIC TIME",
          "color": "modifier",
          "text": "月よう日"
        },
        {
          "label": "PARTICLE",
          "color": "connector",
          "text": "に"
        },
        {
          "label": "EVENT",
          "color": "verb",
          "text": "..."
        }
      ],
      "meaning": "'on [day]' / 'on the [date]' — pinning an event to a fixed point in time",
      "explanation": "に marks a specific, fixed time — a particular day of the week, a specific date, or a set time. Think of it as a pin: it anchors what happens to an exact point on the calendar. Without に, the sentence just floats in time.",
      "notes": [
        "Specific time words TAKE に: 月曜日に (on Monday), 一日に (on the 1st).",
        "Relative/floating time words do NOT take に: 毎日 ✗, 今日 ✗, 今月 ✗.",
        "Quick test: Can you point to it on a calendar? → に. Is it a moving or relative concept? → no に.",
        "Later you will use に with clock times (三時に = at 3 o'clock) and destinations — all the same 'pinpoint' idea."
      ],
      "examples": [
        {
          "parts": [
            {
              "text": "月よう日",
              "role": "time",
              "gloss": "Monday"
            },
            {
              "text": "に",
              "role": "particle"
            },
            {
              "text": "います",
              "role": "verb",
              "gloss": "is here"
            }
          ],
          "en": "She is here on Monday.",
          "breakdown": "月よう日 = specific day → に ✓"
        },
        {
          "parts": [
            {
              "text": "毎日",
              "role": "time",
              "gloss": "every day"
            },
            {
              "text": "います",
              "role": "verb",
              "gloss": "is here"
            }
          ],
          "en": "She is here every day. (no に)",
          "breakdown": "毎日 = relative/floating → no に ✗"
        },
        {
          "parts": [
            {
              "text": "金よう日",
              "role": "time",
              "gloss": "Friday"
            },
            {
              "text": "に",
              "role": "particle"
            },
            {
              "text": "お金",
              "role": "subject",
              "gloss": "money"
            },
            {
              "text": "が",
              "role": "particle"
            },
            {
              "text": "あります",
              "role": "verb",
              "gloss": "there is"
            }
          ],
          "en": "On Friday, there is money.",
          "breakdown": "金よう日 = specific day → に ✓"
        }
      ]
    },
